                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Sumter So. Ca.</placeName>\n                <date>May 13th/58</date>\n            </p>\n            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Knowing your ability to<lb/> diffuse lights on a subject that I\n                am<lb/> comparatively ignorant of, and believing<lb/> in your perfect willingness to\n                aid the<lb/> benighted. I propose asking you a<lb/> few questions on the subject of\n                our<lb/> religion. I unfortunately have been <lb/>very imperfectly instructed\n                myself<lb/> &amp; living as I do out of a congregation<lb/> have no means of\n                instructing my<lb/> children; I have a son a youth of<lb/> 17, whose mind is very\n                mature<lb/> circumstances have induced him<lb/> to open a correspondence with\n                me<lb/> on the subject of religion &amp; he pro<lb/> pounds the following questions\n                to me.</p>\n            <p>1 Why are you a Jew?</p>\n            <p>2 What are the fundamental grounds<lb/> of the Jewish belief? 3 What are<lb/> your\n                ideas of a saviour? 4<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> What<lb/> is your belief in regard to\n                salvation<lb/> &amp; damnation? 5<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Do you believe in<lb/> the\n                divinity of the Bible, or do you<lb/> think it an allegory? These he says</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bg2hw7x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
